                    <span>I stopped after the first 300 pages or so, because the detailed game descriptions were just getting to be too much. I felt like I never got to know anything about Johnson the man, or his life, or the times that he  lived in. If you like reading those expanded box scores that they usually  have in USA Today during the World Series, and which tell every play in the  game, then this is the book for you.</span>
                  
              
